Q 1. In Data Science buzz words, try to understand what companies are expecting from candidates. You can scrap the JDs from the links given in excel sheet. You have to come with 3-4 slides presenting you insights.

job_d = jd$JD

job_data = jd$JD

custom_words = c("https","techniques","develop","developed","etc","required","necessary","strong","preferred","server","using","work","knowledge","large","team","teams","will","information","solutions","years","sources")

Creating a Corpus

jd_doc = VCorpus(VectorSource(job_data))


jd_doc=tm_map(jd_doc,removeNumbers)

jd_doc=tm_map(jd_doc,content_transformer(tolower))

jd_doc=tm_map(jd_doc,removePunctuation)

jd_doc=tm_map(jd_doc,removeWords,stopwords(kind = "english"))

jd_doc=tm_map(jd_doc,removeWords,custom_words)

jd_doc=tm_map(jd_doc,stripWhitespace)

DTM matrix

jd_dtm =DocumentTermMatrix(jd_doc)
jd_dtml = as.matrix(jd_dtm)

dtm_sum = colSums(jd_dtml)

jd_df = data.frame(words=names(dtm_sum),freq=dtm_sum)

wordcloud2(jd_df %>% arrange(-freq), size=1.5,color="random-dark",backgroundColor = "gray")
## Warning: package 'bindrcpp' was built under R version 3.4.3

Here we are creating a Bigram

BigramTokenizer = function(x)NGramTokenizer(x,Weka_control(min=2,max=2))

DTM.bigram = DocumentTermMatrix(jd_doc,control = list(tokenize = BigramTokenizer))

DTM bigram Matrix

matrix = as.matrix(DTM.bigram)

bigram_data = sort(colSums(matrix),decreasing = T)

bigram_df = data.frame(words=names(bigram_data),freq = bigram_data)

wordcloud2(bigram_df, size=1.5,color="random-dark",backgroundColor = "gray")

Q 2. Using the tweets from @narendramodi and do the following:

a. Create a word cloud using the hashtags used in his tweets.

modi_htag = modi[modi$hashtags_count!=0,]
tweets<-sub(".*#", "", modi_htag$text)


tweets_words  = word(tweets)

tweets_w1 = grep("tweets_words", iconv(tweets_words, "latin1", "ASCII", sub="tweets_words"))

tweets_words = tweets_words[-tweets_w1]

length(tweets_words)
## [1] 641

Creating the corpus here

doc = VCorpus(VectorSource(tweets_words))

Removing punctuation,numbers,removewords,stopwords from document

doc = tm_map(doc,removePunctuation)
doc = tm_map(doc,content_transformer(tolower))

Removing other words like : http, https and rt

doc = tm_map(doc, removeWords, custom_words)

Creating DTM

dtm = DocumentTermMatrix(doc)

b ) For each quarter, identify top 5 hashtags based on frequency. Represent them using bar charts.

hashtag = sub(".*#", "", modi_htag$text)

tweet_htag_word = word(hashtag)

Extract date column

date <- as.character(modi_htag$created_at)

date<-as.Date(date ,format = "%d-%m-%Y %H:%M")

Dividing in Quarters as per Financial Year - Apr, May, June - Q1 July, Aug, Sept - Q2 Oct, Nov, Dec - Q3 Jan, Feb, Mar - Q4

top_5 <- data.frame(word=tweet_htag_word ,month = month(date))

top_5$quarter<- ifelse(top_5$month %in% c(1,2,3),"Q4",
                            ifelse(top_5$month %in% c(4,5,6),"Q1",
                           ifelse(top_5$month %in% c(7,8,9),"Q2","Q3")))
top5 = top_5%>%group_by(word,quarter)%>%count()%>%arrange(quarter,-n)
top5 = do.call(rbind, lapply(split(top5,as.character(top5$quarter)), function(x) x[(1:5),]))
top5%>%ggplot(aes(x=word,y=n))+geom_bar(stat = "Identity",aes(fill= word))+facet_grid(.~quarter)+theme(axis.text.x = element_blank())+xlab("word")+ylab("Frequency")+theme(axis.ticks = element_blank())
